# Data Mapping Rules

## Critical Import Rules

1. **Never put labor in COGS.** If an account contains Labor, Wages, or Payroll in the COGS section, map to employee_direct_labor or subcontractors. Never cogs.
2. **Never double-count owner pay.** If detected in both COGS and Expenses, use Expenses only. Flag COGS amount.
3. **Sum, never overwrite.** Multiple accounts mapping to the same field are added together.
4. **Negative income goes to flagged.** Never include in revenue automatically.
5. **Skip subtotals.** Never sum a subtotal row with its component rows.
6. **Hard block on unmatched accounts over $1,000.** Owner must assign before proceeding.
7. **Coverage check.** If mapped_total / source_total < 0.95, show warning.

## Monthly Data Handling

- The P&L template is monthly only. 48 columns. One per month.
- Multi-month Excel exports: sum the last 12 month columns (rolling TTM).
- Weekly/daily data: aggregate to monthly before writing to template.
- Never attempt to write weekly granularity to the P&L template.

## Owner Pay Split Defaults

| Business Type | Direct Labor % | Management % |
|---|---|---|
| solo_service (under $200K) | 70% | 30% |
| small_team (2-5 employees) | 50% | 50% |
| larger_team (6+) | 30% | 70% |
| retail_product | 40% | 60% |
| unknown | 50% | 50% |

## Mapping Pipeline Order

1. Parse QBO report (flatten, skip subtotals, preserve negative amounts)
2. Rule-based mapper (exact name match, then substring, then section default)
3. AI classifier (Claude Haiku, only for unmatched Income/COGS accounts)
4. Confirmation builder (confidence tiers, error prevention, live P&L preview)
5. Expense/OtherExpense accounts with no name match default to other_opex. No AI call needed.
